Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA) is a licensed registered nurse with advanced specialized training in the administration of anesthesia. The CRNA administers, monitors, and adjusts anesthetic doses to individual patients, from neonatal through geriatrics, during surgery and other procedures as follows:
Selects and administers anesthetic techniques, medications, and adjunctive drugs according to accepted departmental guidelines.
Identifies and manages emergency situations according to departmental policies and procedures.
Induces and maintains general anesthesia at required and safe levels, using techniques prescribed by the assigned staff anesthesiologist or techniques customarily used within the department.
Performs basic perioperative diagnosis testing and documentation to the anesthetic record.

Job Title: CRNA (Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist), Aria Health Physician Services, Torresdale Campus Full time (40 hours per week)
Job Description:
Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist is responsible for assessing, diagnosing and treating patients throughout the perioperative phase. The CRNA is accountable to patients for the delivery of appropriate, effective quality nursing and anesthesia care and services consistent with the ANA Code for Nurses, Standards of Nursing Practice and Patient Care Standards established by the Department of Anesthesia.

Reviews charts, identifies patient and surgical procedures and insures that each patient's permit and date are completed prior to administering anesthesia. If permit or date is incomplete, reports this information to the Anesthesiologist. Insures that anesthesia pre-op note has been completed for each patient and that anesthetic plan has been discussed with the Anesthesiologist prior to the patient's arrival in the O.R. suite and documented.

Obtains IV access and administers fluids.

Administers prescribed anesthesia under the supervision and guidance of the Anesthesiologist. Anesthesia including general endotracheal anesthesia, general anesthesia with mask or LMA, regional anesthesia and monitored anesthesia care (MAC).

Ensures the availability of equipment and drugs to be used for various O.R. procedures by checking the equipment between cases and also by completing a safety checklist. Demonstrates a current working knowledge and ability to use all equipment.

Maintains a constant and accurate record on each patient from the commencement of anesthesia until the time when the patient is relinquished to the designated post-anesthesia area. Performs this function as evidenced by the accurate completion of the anesthesia record, also ensuring that the MD has signed each record.

Notifies the Anesthesiologist immediately at the first sign of an unexpected event in either the O.R. or PACU.

Initiates transfusion therapy in the O.R. or PACU and reviews pertinent lab studies after consulting first with the Anesthesiologist. Performs this function as evidenced by the completed transfusion form.

Cleans and stocks rooms after each case when anesthesia technician is unavailable as evidenced by the smooth transition (no delay) from one case to another.

Participate in IV consults on patient floors as evidenced by the accurate completion of the consultation form.

Participates and/or performs Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation in the O.R., PACU or any other area of the Hospital as needed and as evidenced by appropriate documentation in the patient's medical record. Attends trauma alerts and Codes.

Attends monthly anesthesia CRNA meetings as evidenced by attendance record sheets, as well as attends local national meetings (as evidenced by proof of obtaining CEU's) in order to keep abreast of new ideas and techniques.

Performs other related duties as required or delegated by the current guidelines suggested by the American Association of Nurse Anesthetists.

Participates in the orientation and continuing education necessary for all individuals who use and/or maintain equipment (e.g. anesthesia machines, monitoring equipment and any other equipment used by department members).

Current Pennsylvania Registered Nurse License (RN)

Current Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist Certificate (CRNA)

Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA) is authorized to perform routine duties on a regular, repetitive basis. Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Qualifications

We are looking for CRNA's with experience & background using ketamine who can provide in-home IV Ketamine infusions. You will be working with patients who have been diagnosed by a board certified psychiatrist with Treatment Resistant Depression (TRD), PTSD and other treatment resistant psychiatric disorders who may benefit from IV Ketamine infusions.
Patients will always be screened for strict inclusion and exclusion criteria by our psychiatry staff through a virtual appointment. If patients meet our criteria, they will be enrolled into future treatments with IV Ketamine, with you in the comfort of their home or the comfort of our offices. You will be paired with a registered nurse as well to assist you with post IV care monitoring.
This is a great opportunity to make a positive impact on patients with TRD while experiencing an excellent income source and great work-life balance.
CRNA's that successfully complete our interview process, will be matched with one of our partner Professional Corporations to start treating patients. You will be provided with a ketamine infusion step by step protocol and training session. We work currently in New York and California and will be opening service in all major cities over the next year. Your placement will be made with your clinical preferences, state license, experience and schedule in mind.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Join our CRNA directed practice as we expand our team to accommodate a 5th OR. This is a lifestyle position, where the goal is to have post-call days off yet you get to practice to the full scope of your practice with full autonomy. This is a CRNA led practice where we have wonderful collegiality with our surgeons and nurse anesthetist staff!
CRNA Facility:
100 bed medical center
Over 100 years of history
Faith based, nonprofit

Responsibilities
Under the supervision of an anesthesiologist, the Nurse Anesthetist (NA) will perform safe anesthesia care, consisting of the following: pre-operative assessment, writing of appropriate pre-op orders as specified by approved standard procedure, administration of all types of anesthetic and techniques, patient monitoring intra-operatively, provides for intra-op course and emergence and assists as necessary in post-operative care. You may be assigned to a combination of 8, 10, or 12 hours shifts, including evening, nights, weekends, and holidays totaling 40 hours per week as well as on call shifts. Work will be assigned to various OR's.

Qualifications
REQUIRED:

a. Graduation from an accredited school of nursing
b. Graduation from an accredited school of nurse anesthesia
c. Valid California Registered Nurse license
d. Valid California Nurse Anesthetist license
e. Current certification/re-certification by the Councils of the American Association of Nurse Anesthetists
f. Valid basic life support certification by the American Heart Association and ability to perform cardiopulmonary resuscitation
g. Valid Advanced Cardiac Life Support certification by the American Heart Association


a. Identification of pre-existing disease entities and their potential impact upon anesthesia care and plan documentation of past medical history, physical examination, laboratory tests, ECG and chest X-ray
b. Understanding interactions of pre-operative drug therapy with proposed anesthetic plan and agents for all age groups
c. Identification of abnormalities on physical examination which pose potential problems in anesthesia management
d. Understanding the medical indications for delay of elective surgery and for pre-operative specialty consultation

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.








Location: Cullman Regional Medical Center · Anesthesia Department (054)
Schedule: Full Time, Days

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.








Location: Cullman Regional Medical Center · Anesthesia Department (054)
Schedule: Full Time, Days

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Schedule: Full Time, Days

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.








Location: Cullman Regional Medical Center · Anesthesia Department (054)
Schedule: Full Time, Days

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Schedule: Full Time, Days

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.








Location: Cullman Regional Medical Center · Anesthesia Department (054)
Schedule: Full Time, Days

Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.








Location: Cullman Regional Medical Center · Anesthesia Department (054)
Schedule: Full Time, Days

Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist (CRNA)
Job Description
The Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetist CRNA will administer anesthetics to patients undergoing medical, dental, and surgical procedures. They will work under the direction of the attending surgeon, dentist, or anesthesiologist. Duties will include getting supplies and equipment ready for procedures, studying and interpreting pre-surgical tests to determine how the anesthetic will affect the patient, and assuring that an adequate blood supply is on hand in case of an emergency.
In addition to administering the prescribed anesthetic, the CRNA will monitor the patient’s vital signs and communicate the information to the physicians. They will also perform other tasks during these medical procedures, such as inserting artificial airways, administering oxygen, and attempting to prevent surgical shock. In addition, they may be required to assist with stabilization of patient and coordination of evacuation of patient to medevac center.








Location: Cullman Regional Medical Center · Anesthesia Department (054)
Schedule: Full Time, Days
